OL,6,FHe said: "This case will proceed on
OL,7,Fthe basis that the allegation is
OL,8,Ffalse."
OL,10,FHe said the BBC would also contend
OL,11,Fthat the allegation did not damage Mr
OL,12,FAdams' reputation.
OL,14,FThe barrister told the jury: "You will
OL,15,Fhave no difficulty coming to a
OL,16,Fdecision on what the article meant,
OL,17,Fthe allegation is front and centre,
OL,18,Fboth in the programme and in the
OL,19,Farticle."
